This paper focuses on the analysis of scientific discourse structures using deep representation learning for information extraction from biomedical literature. The paper specifically applies clause-level sequence tagging for a set of discourse types on scientific paragraphs. This work involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval, which are all relevant to the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Deep Learning (cs.DL).
